#D-KB ID: statements13Formula1 (gdprC2A6P4ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x processes ?w's personal data during the interval ?t1 (and that data is controlled by ?y, who appointed ?x), and: (1) the purpose ?epup for processing is different from the purpose ?epuc for collecting the data, (2) ?w did not give consent for ?epup, and (3) the processing is not necessary under European Union or Member State law to safeguard the objectives listed in Article 23(1) GDPR, then ?y is obliged to consider any link between ?epup and ?epuc, the context of the processing ?ep, the nature of ?w, and each ?ecs that results from ?ep and is foreseen by ?w. This is an example where a single rule in the D-KB must correspond to multiple rules in Deontic Logic Reified. Each factor (the link, the context, the nature of the data subject, and the envisaged consequences) must be evaluated independently, assuming that any one of them may apply even if the others do not. Therefore, the rule must be split into separate rules.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements13Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
