	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?egc rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu. BIND(BNode() AS ?ed) NOT EXISTS{?edr rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?edr rdf:type :Demonstrate. ?edr :has-time ?t1. ?edr :has-agent ?y. ?edr :has-object ?egc. ?edr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements14Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements15Formula1 (gdprC2A7P2ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If x is processing w's personal data during the interval t1 (and the data is controlled by y, who appointed x), and the data subject gave consent for the purpose epu, but that consent was obtained within a written declaration that also concerns other matters, then y must ensure that the request for consent is presented clearly and kept separate from those other matters.
