#D-KB ID: statements16Formula2 (gdprC2A7P3ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the data subject is allowed to withdraw consent at any time, either as inferred by the preceding rule or because it is explicitly recorded in the knowledge graph, the processor must inform the data subject of this right.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements16Formula2"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ec rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?ec rdf:type :Communicate. ?ec :has-agent ?x. ?ec :has-object ?ew. ?ec :has-recipient ?w. ?ec :has-time ?t1. ?ec :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements16Formula2"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu. ?ew rdf:type :Permitted. ?ew :has-time ?t1. ?ew rdf:type :Withdraw. ?ew :has-agent ?w. ?ew :has-object ?c. BIND(BNode() AS ?ec) NOT EXISTS{?ecr rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?ecr rdf:type :Communicate. ?ecr :has-agent ?x. ?ecr :has-object ?ew. ?ecr :has-recipient ?w. ?ecr :has-time ?t1. ?ecr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements16Formula2"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements16Formula3 (gdprC2A7P3ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x processes ?w's personal data during the interval ?t1 (with the data controlled by ?y, who appointed ?x), and the processing is based on the data subject's consent, and ?w is permitted to withdraw consent at any time (as inferred by statements16Formula1 or because it is already explicitly asserted in the knowledge graph), then ?x is obliged to ensure that withdrawing consent is as easy as giving it throughout the entire interval ?t1. This rule uses the thematic role has-object-state to indicate that the withdrawal must be easy, and has-object-state-as to specify the comparative reference: it must be as easy as giving consent.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements16Formula3"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?eea rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eea :has-time ?t1. ?eea rdf:type :Keep. ?eea :has-agent ?x. ?eea :has-object ?ew. ?eea :has-object-state :easy. ?eea :has-object-state-as ?egc. ?eea :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements16Formula3"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?egc rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu. ?ew rdf:type :Permitted. ?ew :has-time ?t1. ?ew rdf:type :Withdraw. ?ew :has-agent ?w. ?ew :has-object ?c. BIND(BNode() AS ?eea) NOT EXISTS{?eear rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eear :has-time ?t1. ?eear rdf:type :Keep. ?eear :has-agent ?x. ?eear :has-object ?ew. ?eear :has-object-state :easy. ?eear :has-object-state-as ?egc. ?eear :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements16Formula3"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements17Formula1 (gdprC2A8P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: This is an exception to the rule in statements17Formula2. If the data subject is under the age of 16, their consent may still be valid, provided that the Member State to which they belong defines a lower minimum age for consent.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements17Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?exx :defeats-on-8-1-ms ?ex. ?exx :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements17Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?ex :checks-exception-in-8-1-ms (?w ?age). ?w :has-member-state/:has-minimal-age-for-consent ?mac. FILTER(?age>=?mac). BIND(BNode() AS ?exx) NOT EXISTS{?exxr :defeats-on-8-1-ms ?ex. ?exxr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements17Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements17Formula2 (gdprC2A8P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: The exception in Article 8(1) involves verifying whether the data subject is under the age of 16. If so, the lawfulness of processing under Article 6(1)(a) does not apply, unless the exception-on-8-1-ms condition holds. This condition checks the minimum age of consent as defined by the data subject's Member State (previous rule).
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements17Formula2"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-8-1 ?el. ?ex :checks-exception-in-8-1-ms (?w ?age). ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements17Formula2"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?el :checks-exception-in-8-1 (?w). ?w :has-age ?age. FILTER(?age<16). BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-8-1 ?el. ?exr :checks-exception-in-8-1-ms (?w ?age). ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements17Formula2"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements17Formula3 (gdprC2A8P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the holder of parental responsibility for the data subject gives consent to the processing of the data subject's personal data, then the processing is lawful without exception.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements17Formula3"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?el rdf:type :Rexist. ?el :has-time ?t1. ?el rdf:type :Keep. ?el :has-agent ?x. ?el :has-object ?ep. ?el :has-object-state :lawful. ?el :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements17Formula3"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?egc rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?h. ?h :is-holder-of-parental-responsibility ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?egc :has-time ?egct. ?egct time:inXSDDateTime ?dtegc. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu. ?t1 time:hasBeginning ?t1b. ?t1b time:inXSDDateTime ?dtbep. FILTER(?dtegc<?dtbep). BIND(BNode() AS ?el) NOT EXISTS{?elr rdf:type :Rexist. ?elr :has-time ?t1. ?elr rdf:type :Keep. ?elr :has-agent ?x. ?elr :has-object ?ep. ?elr :has-object-state :lawful. ?elr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements17Formula3"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements18Formula1 (gdprC2A8P2ref)
#DESCRIPTION: The data controller is obliged to ascertain (make reasonable efforts to verify) that the holder of parental responsibility for the data subject has given consent to the processing of the data subject's personal data.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements18Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ev rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?ev rdf:type :Ascertain. ?ev :has-time ?t2. ?ev :has-agent ?y. ?ev :has-object ?egc. ?ev :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements18Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?egc rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?h. ?h :is-holder-of-parental-responsibility ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?t1 time:hasBeginning ?t1b. ?mi rdf:type time:Instant. ?mi rdf:type :minusInfinity. ?t2 rdf:type time:Interval. ?t2 time:hasBeginning ?mi. ?t2 time:hasEnd ?t1b. BIND(BNode() AS ?ev) NOT EXISTS{?evr rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?evr rdf:type :Ascertain. ?evr :has-time ?t2. ?evr :has-agent ?y. ?evr :has-object ?egc. ?evr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements18Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9 (gdprC2A9P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: A processor ?x, nominated by a controller ?y who controls the personal data ?z of a data subject ?w, is prohibited from processing these data if they are sensitive data, unless one of the exceptions in Article 9(2) applies.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{<<?enp rdf:type :A-Permitted>> rdf:type :false. ?enp rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?enp :has-agent ?x. ?enp :has-object ?z. ?enp :has-time ?t1. ?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?enp :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?z rdf:type :SensitiveData. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. BIND(BNode() AS ?enp) NOT EXISTS{<<?enpr rdf:type :A-Permitted>> rdf:type :false. ?enpr rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?enpr :has-agent ?x. ?enpr :has-object ?z. ?enpr :has-time ?t1. ?enpr :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?enpr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction (gdprC2A9P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: The following rules were introduced as a more effective alternative to modelling the predicate "or" from Hobbs' framework. If the data ?d is either EthicalData, OpinionData, ..., or SexualOrientationData, then it is also classified as an data of type 'SensitiveData', which is the predicate used in the previous formula.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :EthicalData.}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :OpinionData.}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :ReligiousOrPhilosophicalBeliefsData.}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :TradeUnionMembership.}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :HealthData.}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :SexualData.}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula1/statements19Formula2/statements19Formula3/statements19Formula4/statements19Formula7/statements19Formula8/statements19Formula9-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?d rdf:type :SensitiveData.}
	WHERE{?d rdf:type :SexualOrientationData.}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements19Formula5 (gdprC2A9P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: A processor ?x, nominated by a controller ?y who controls the personal data ?z of a data subject ?w, is prohibited from processing these data if they are genetic data and the purpose is to identify the data subject, unless one of the exceptions in Article 9(2) applies.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula5"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{<<?enp rdf:type :A-Permitted>> rdf:type :false. ?enp rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?enp :has-agent ?x. ?enp :has-object ?z. ?enp :has-time ?t1. ?enp :is-based-on ?id. ?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?id). ?enp :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements19Formula5"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?z rdf:type :GeneticData. ?id rdf:type :Purpose. ?id :is-identification-of ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?enp) NOT EXISTS{<<?enpr rdf:type :A-Permitted>> rdf:type :false. ?enpr rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?enpr :has-agent ?x. ?enpr :has-object ?z. ?enpr :has-time ?t1. ?enpr :is-based-on ?id. ?enpr :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?id). ?enpr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements19Formula5"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements19Formula6 (gdprC2A9P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: A processor ?x, nominated by a controller ?y who controls the personal data ?z of a data subject ?w, is prohibited from processing these data if they are biometric data and the purpose is to identify the data subject, unless one of the exceptions in Article 9(2) applies.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements19Formula6"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{<<?enp rdf:type :A-Permitted>> rdf:type :false. ?enp rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?enp :has-agent ?x. ?enp :has-object ?z. ?enp :has-time ?t1. ?enp :is-based-on ?id. ?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?id). ?enp :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements19Formula6"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?z rdf:type :BiometricData. ?id rdf:type :Purpose. ?id :is-identification-of ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?enp) NOT EXISTS{<<?enpr rdf:type :A-Permitted>> rdf:type :false. ?enpr rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?enpr :has-agent ?x. ?enpr :has-object ?z. ?enpr :has-time ?t1. ?enpr :is-based-on ?id. ?enpr :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?id). ?enpr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements19Formula6"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements20Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the data subject ?w has given consent to the processing, then the exception under Article 9(2) applies, and the processing is not prohibited, unless one of the exceptions under Article 8(1) or Article 9(2)(1) also applies.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements20Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :checks-exception-in-9-2-a (?egc). ?ex :checks-exception-in-8-1 (?w). ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements20Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?egc rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu. ?egc :has-time/time:inXSDDateTime ?dtegc. ?t1 time:hasBeginning/time:inXSDDateTime ?dtbep. FILTER(?dtegc<?dtbep). BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :checks-exception-in-9-2-a (?egc). ?exr :checks-exception-in-8-1 (?w). ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements20Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements20Formula2 (gdprC2A9P2p1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: if there is a European Union or Member State law ?l that does not authorize the action ?egc, then exception-on-9-2-a applies.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements20Formula2"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?exx :defeats-on-9-2-a ?ex. ?exx :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements20Formula2"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?ex :checks-exception-in-9-2-a (?egc). ?ena rdf:type :Rexist. ?ena :not ?ea. ?ea rdf:type :Authorize. ?ea :has-agent ?l. ?ea :has-object ?egc. ?l rdf:type :EUorMSlaw. BIND(BNode() AS ?exx) NOT EXISTS{?exxr :defeats-on-9-2-a ?ex. ?exxr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements20Formula2"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements21Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p2ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the processing is necessary for either an obligation or a right of the data controller or the data subject related to employment, social security, or social protection law, and the processing is authorized by European or Member State law, or by a collective agreement related to such a law that provides appropriate safeguards for the fundamental rights and interests of the data subject, then the processing is not prohibited; that is, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements21Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements21Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?eorcd. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?eorcd :is-related-to ?ss. ?ss rdf:type :EmploymentAndSocialSecurityAndSocialProtectionLaw. {?eorcd rdf:type :Obligatory.}UNION{?eorcd rdf:type :Permitted.}. {?eorcd :has-agent ?y.}UNION{?eorcd :has-agent ?w.}. ?l rdf:type :EUorMSlaw. ?ea rdf:type :Rexist. ?ea rdf:type :Authorize. ?ea :has-object ?ep. {?ea :has-agent ?l.}UNION{?ea :has-agent ?c. ?c rdf:type :CollectiveAgreement. ?c :is-related-to ?l. ?es rdf:type :Rexist. ?es rdf:type :Safeguard. ?es :has-agent ?c. ?es :has-object ?rf. ?rf :rights-and-freedoms-of ?w.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements21Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements22Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p3ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the processing is necessary to protect the vital interests of the data subject or of another natural person where the data subject is not able to give consent, then the processing is not prohibited; that is, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements22Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements22Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?epr. ?epr rdf:type :Protect. ?epr :has-object ?vi. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. {?vi :vital-interest-of ?w.}UNION{?vi :vital-interest-of ?p. ?p rdf:type :Person. ?ena rdf:type :Rexist. ?ena :not ?ea. ?ea rdf:type :BeAbleTo. ?ea :has-time ?t1. ?ea :has-agent ?w. ?ea :has-object ?egc. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?c :is-consent-for ?epu.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements22Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements23Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p4ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the controller is a not-for-profit association, and the processing is necessary for one of its activities, and the data subject is a member, former member, or otherwise related to the association, and the personal data are not disclosed outside the association (or are only disclosed with the data subject's consent), then the processing is not prohibited; that is, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements23Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements23Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?x rdf:type :NotForProfitBody. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?eac. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?eac :is-related-to ?x. ?w :is-related-to ?x. ?ec rdf:type :Communicate. ?ec :has-agent ?x. ?ec :has-object ?z. ?ec :has-recipient ?k. ?k :is-outside ?x. {?enc :not ?ec. ?enc rdf:type :Rexist.}UNION{?ec rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Rexist. ?egc rdf:type :Give. ?egc :has-agent ?w. ?egc :has-object ?c. ?c :is-consent-for ?ec.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements23Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements24Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p5ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the data are public, then the processing is not prohibited; that is, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements24Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements24Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?z rdf:type :Public. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements24Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements25Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p6ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the processing is necessary for either a legal claim or for some court, then the processing is not prohibited; that is, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements25Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements25Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?en1 rdf:type :Rexist. ?en1 rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en1 :has-agent ?ep. ?en1 :has-object ?lc. {?lc rdf:type :LegalClaim.}UNION{?lc rdf:type :Court.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements25Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements26Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p7ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the processing is necessary for reasons of public interest and is carried out under a European or Member State law that is considered reasonable (meaning that it is proportionate to the aim pursued, respects the essence of the right to data protection) and that provides appropriate safeguards for the data subject's rights and freedoms and legitimate interests, then the processing is not prohibited. In other words, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements26Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements26Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?et. ?et :is-related-to ?pp. ?pp rdf:type :PublicInterest. ?et :is-related-to ?l. ?l rdf:type :EUorMSlaw. ?l rdf:type :Reasonable. ?es1 rdf:type :Rexist. ?es1 rdf:type :Safeguard. ?es1 :has-agent ?l. ?es1 :has-object ?rf. ?rf :rights-and-freedoms-of ?w. ?es2 rdf:type :Rexist. ?es2 rdf:type :Safeguard. ?es2 :has-agent ?l. ?es2 :has-object ?li. ?li :legitimate-interest-of ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements26Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements27Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p8ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the processing is necessary to execute a task related to health (here intended as "preventive or occupational medicine...the management of health or social care systems and services") and this is authorized either by a law of the EU or a Member State or a contract related to an health professional, then the processing is not prohibited. In other words, Article 9(1) of the GDPR does not apply.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements27Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements27Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?ee. ?ee rdf:type :Execute. ?ee :has-object ?et. ?et :is-related-to ?h. ?h rdf:type :Health. ?ea rdf:type :Rexist. ?ea rdf:type :Authorize. ?ea :has-object ?et. {?ea :has-agent ?l. ?l rdf:type :EUorMSlaw.}UNION{?ea :has-agent ?c. ?c rdf:type :Contract. ?c :is-related-to ?hp. ?hp rdf:type :HealthProfessional.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements27Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements28Formula1 (gdprC2A9P2p9ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the processing is necessary to carry out a task in the public interest related to public health, and this is authorized by EU or Member State law that safeguards the rights and freedoms of the data subject, then the processing is not prohibited.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements28Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements28Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?enp :checks-exception-in-9-2 (?w ?t1 ?x ?z ?epu). ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?ee. ?ee rdf:type :Execute. ?ee :has-object ?et. ?et :is-related-to ?pi. ?pi rdf:type :PublicInterest. ?pi :is-related-to ?h. ?h rdf:type :Health. ?ea rdf:type :Rexist. ?ea rdf:type :Authorize. ?ea :has-agent ?l. ?ea :has-object ?et. ?l rdf:type :EUorMSlaw. ?es rdf:type :Rexist. ?es rdf:type :Safeguard. ?es :has-agent ?l. ?es :has-object ?rf. ?rf :rights-and-freedoms-of ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-9-2 ?enp. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements28Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements29Formula1 (gdprC2A10P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If  ?x is processing  ?w's personal data during the interval  ?t1 (and the data is controlled by  ?y, who appointed  ?x), and the processing is related to a crime, then the processing must either be carried out under the supervision of an official authority or be authorised by Union or Member State law that provides appropriate safeguards for the rights and freedoms of data subjects. As in statements4Formula2 above, there is a disjunction in the consequent, which is implemented by the next two rules.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements29Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?eo rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eo rdf:type :MakeControlledOrAuthorized. ?eo :has-agent ?y. ?eo :has-object ?ep. ?eo :has-time ?t1. ?eo :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :is-related-to ?c. ?c rdf:type :Crime. BIND(BNode() AS ?eo) NOT EXISTS{?eor rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eor rdf:type :MakeControlledOrAuthorized. ?eor :has-agent ?y. ?eor :has-object ?ep. ?eor :has-time ?t1. ?eor :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements29Formula1-disjunction (gdprC2A10P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: The following rules were introduced as a more effective alternative to modelling the predicate "or" from Hobbs' framework. If the processing is controlled by an official authority, or is authorised by EU or Member State law that safeguards the rights and freedoms of the data subject, then the processing is classified as 'MakeControlledOrAuthorized'.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements29Formula1-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?emcoa rdf:type :Rexist. ?emcoa rdf:type :MakeControlledOrAuthorized. ?emcoa :has-agent ?y. ?emcoa :has-object ?ep. ?emcoa :has-time ?t1. ?emcoa :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula1-disjunction"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?e rdf:type :Rexist. ?e rdf:type :Control. ?e :has-agent ?oa. ?e :has-object ?ep. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?e :has-time ?t1. ?oa rdf:type :OfficialAuthority. BIND(BNode() AS ?emcoa) NOT EXISTS{?emcoar rdf:type :Rexist. ?emcoar rdf:type :MakeControlledOrAuthorized. ?emcoar :has-agent ?y. ?emcoar :has-object ?ep. ?emcoar :has-time ?t1. ?emcoar :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula1-disjunction"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements29Formula1-disjunction"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?emcoa rdf:type :Rexist. ?emcoa rdf:type :MakeControlledOrAuthorized. ?emcoa :has-agent ?y. ?emcoa :has-object ?ep. ?emcoa :has-time ?t1. ?emcoa :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula1-disjunction"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?e rdf:type :Rexist. ?e rdf:type :Authorize. ?e :has-agent ?l. ?e :has-object ?ep. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?e :has-time ?t1. ?l rdf:type :EUorMSlaw. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?es rdf:type :Rexist. ?es1 rdf:type :Safeguard. ?es1 :has-agent ?l. ?es1 :has-object ?rf. ?rf :rights-and-freedoms-of ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?emcoa) NOT EXISTS{?emcoar rdf:type :Rexist. ?emcoar rdf:type :MakeControlledOrAuthorized. ?emcoar :has-agent ?y. ?emcoar :has-object ?ep. ?emcoar :has-time ?t1. ?emcoar :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula1-disjunction"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements29Formula2 (gdprC2A10P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x is processing ?w's personal data during the interval ?t1 (with the data controlled by ?y, who appointed ?x), and the processing relates to a crime, and the data are stored in a personal data record ?pdr, then ?pdr must be controlled by an official authority. Note that this introduces an existential quantifier in the consequent: the agent must be an official authority, but we do not specify which one. We model this by introducing new thematic roles (such as :has-agent-type, and similarly :has-object-type, etc.). The agent, whoever it is, is required to have this type. This is enforced by the next rule, which currently applies to :Control only, but could be generalised.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements29Formula2"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?eo rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eo rdf:type :Control. ?eo :has-agent-type :OfficialAuthority. ?eo :has-object ?pdr. ?eo :has-time ?t1. ?eo :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula2"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?ep :is-related-to ?c. ?c rdf:type :Crime. ?es rdf:type :Store. ?es rdf:type :Rexist. ?es :has-agent ?x. ?es :has-object ?z. ?es :has-location ?pdr. ?es :has-time ?t1. ?pdr rdf:type :PersonalDataRecord. BIND(BNode() AS ?eo) NOT EXISTS{?eor rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eor rdf:type :Control. ?eor :has-agent-type :OfficialAuthority. ?eor :has-object ?pdr. ?eor :has-time ?t1. ?eor :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements29Formula2"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements29Formula2-existential (gdprC2A10P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: this rule implements the existential quantifiers described in the previous rule.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements29Formula2-existential"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?e :has-agent-type :OfficialAuthority.}
	WHERE{?e rdf:type :Control. ?e :has-agent ?oa. ?oa rdf:type :OfficialAuthority.}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements30Formula1 (gdprC2A11P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x is processing ?w’s personal data during the interval ?t1 (with the data controlled by ?y, who appointed ?x), but the identification of ?w is no longer necessary for the processing, then ?y is not obliged to store, process, or collect additional information ?a with the aim of identifying ?w.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{<<?esa rdf:type :A-Obligatory>> rdf:type :false. ?esa rdf:type :Store. ?esa :has-agent ?y. ?esa :has-object ?a. ?esa :has-aim ?eid. <<?epa rdf:type :A-Obligatory>> rdf:type :false. ?epa rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?epa :has-agent ?y. ?epa :has-object ?a. ?epa :has-aim ?eid. <<?eca rdf:type :A-Obligatory>> rdf:type :false. ?eca rdf:type :CollectPersonalData. ?eca :has-agent ?y. ?eca :has-object ?a. ?eca :has-aim ?eid. ?esa :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string. ?eca :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string. ?epa :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?enn rdf:type :Rexist. ?enn :not ?en. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?eid. ?en :has-object ?epu. ?eid rdf:type :Identify. ?eid :has-object ?w. ?a :information-about ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?esa) BIND(BNode() AS ?eca) BIND(BNode() AS ?epa) NOT EXISTS{<<?esar rdf:type :A-Obligatory>> rdf:type :false. ?esar rdf:type :Store. ?esar :has-agent ?y. ?esar :has-object ?a. ?esar :has-aim ?eid. <<?epar rdf:type :A-Obligatory>> rdf:type :false. ?epar rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?epar :has-agent ?y. ?epar :has-object ?a. ?epar :has-aim ?eid. <<?ecar rdf:type :A-Obligatory>> rdf:type :false. ?ecar rdf:type :CollectPersonalData. ?ecar :has-agent ?y. ?ecar :has-object ?a. ?ecar :has-aim ?eid. ?esar :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string. ?ecar :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string. ?epar :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements30Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements31Formula1 (gdprC2A11P2ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x is processing ?w’s personal data during the interval ?t1 (with the data controlled by ?y, who appointed ?x), but the identification of ?w is no longer necessary for the processing and ?y demonstrates that they are unable to identify ?w, then ?y is obliged to communicate this to ?w.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements31Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ec rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?ec rdf:type :Communicate. ?ec :has-agent ?y. ?ec :has-object ?ena. ?ec :has-recipient ?w. ?ec :has-time ?t2. ?ec :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements31Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?enn rdf:type :Rexist. ?enn :not ?en. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-time ?t1. ?en :has-agent ?eid. ?en :has-object ?epu. ?eid rdf:type :Identify. ?eid :has-object ?w. ?ed rdf:type :Rexist. ?ed rdf:type :Demonstrate. ?ed :has-time ?t1. ?ed :has-agent ?y. ?ed :has-object ?ena. ?ena :not ?ea. ?ea rdf:type :BeAbleTo. ?ea :has-time ?t1. ?ea :has-agent ?y. ?ea :has-object ?eid. ?t2 :is-without-delay ?t1. BIND(BNode() AS ?ec) NOT EXISTS{?ecr rdf:type :A-Obligatory. ?ecr rdf:type :Communicate. ?ecr :has-agent ?y. ?ecr :has-object ?ena. ?ecr :has-recipient ?w. ?ecr :has-time ?t2. ?ecr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements31Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements108Formula1 (gdprC3S4A21P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x is processing ?w's personal data during the interval ?t1 (and this data is controlled by ?y, who nominated ?x), and processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller, then the data subject is permitted to object to the processing.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements108Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?eo rdf:type :A-Permitted. ?eo :has-time ?t1. ?eo rdf:type :Object. ?eo :has-agent ?w. ?eo :has-object ?ep. ?eo :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?ee. ?ee rdf:type :Execute. ?ee :has-object ?et. ?et :is-related-to ?p. {?p rdf:type :PublicInterest.}UNION{?p rdf:type :PublicPowers. ?e rdf:type :Rexist. ?e rdf:type :Hold. ?e :has-agent ?y. ?e :has-object ?p.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?eo) NOT EXISTS{?eor rdf:type :A-Permitted. ?eor :has-time ?t1. ?eor rdf:type :Object. ?eor :has-agent ?w. ?eor :has-object ?ep. ?eor :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements108Formula2 (gdprC3S4A21P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If  ?x  is processing  ?w's personal data during the interval  ?t1  (and the data is controlled by  ?y, who appointed  ?x), and the processing is necessary for the legitimate interests of either the controller or a third party, then the data subject is permitted to object to the processing.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements108Formula2"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?eo rdf:type :A-Permitted. ?eo :has-time ?t1. ?eo rdf:type :Object. ?eo :has-agent ?w. ?eo :has-object ?ep. ?eo :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula2"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?li. {?li :legitimate-interest-of ?y.}UNION{?li :legitimate-interest-of ?tp. ?tp rdf:type :ThirdParty.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?eo) NOT EXISTS{?eor rdf:type :A-Permitted. ?eor :has-time ?t1. ?eor rdf:type :Object. ?eor :has-agent ?w. ?eor :has-object ?ep. ?eor :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula2"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements108Formula3 (gdprC3S4A21P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If  ?x  is processing  ?w's personal data during the interval  ?t1  (and the data is controlled by  ?y, who appointed  ?x), and the processing is carried out by public authorities in the performance of their tasks, then the data subject is permitted to withdraw his consent.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements108Formula3"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?eo rdf:type :A-Permitted. ?eo :has-time ?t1. ?eo rdf:type :Object. ?eo :has-agent ?w. ?eo :has-object ?ep. ?eo :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula3"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?en rdf:type :Rexist. ?en rdf:type :BeNecessaryFor. ?en :has-agent ?ep. ?en :has-object ?ee. ?ee rdf:type :Execute. ?ee :has-agent ?pb. ?ee :has-object ?et. ?pb rdf:type :Public_Body. BIND(BNode() AS ?eo) NOT EXISTS{?eor rdf:type :A-Permitted. ?eor :has-time ?t1. ?eor rdf:type :Object. ?eor :has-agent ?w. ?eor :has-object ?ep. ?eor :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula3"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements108Formula4/statements108Formula5/statements108Formula6 (gdprC3S4A21P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: This rule checks the exception :checks-exception-in-21-1. If ?x processes ?w's personal data during the interval ?t1 (and that data is controlled by ?y, who nominated ?x), and the processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller, but the data subject has withdrawn consent, then the exception applies. NB. statements108Formula4, statements108Formula5, and statements108Formula6 are in fact the same SPARQL rule. Under negation-as-failure they appear as three separate rules (because the antecedents of the corresponding D-KB rules differ), but once negation-as-failure is translated into superiority relations, these three rules collapse into a single rule. In other words, this rule base is not fully one-to-one aligned with the D-KB. This is an example where three rules in the D-KB correspond to a single rule here; the opposite also occurs, for instance when disjunction is implemented, where one D-KB rule corresponds to multiple rules here.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements108Formula4/statements108Formula5/statements108Formula6"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-21-1 ?el. ?ex :checks-exception-in-21-1-NW (?ep ?w ?y). ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula4/statements108Formula5/statements108Formula6"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?el :checks-exception-in-21-1 (?t1 ?w ?ep ?y). ?eo rdf:type :Rexist. ?eo :has-time ?t2. ?eo rdf:type :Object. ?eo :has-agent ?w. ?eo :has-object ?ep. ?t1 time:hasEnd ?t1e. ?t1e time:inXSDDateTime ?dtt1e. ?t2 time:inXSDDateTime ?dtt2. FILTER(?dtt2<?dtt1e). BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-21-1 ?el. ?exr :checks-exception-in-21-1-NW (?ep ?w ?y). ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula4/statements108Formula5/statements108Formula6"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements108Formula7/statements108Formula8/statements108Formula9 (gdprC3S4A21P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If ?x processes ?w's personal data during the interval ?t1 (and that data is controlled by ?y, who nominated ?x), and the processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the controller, but either (i) the controller demonstrates compelling legitimate grounds for the processing that override the interests, rights, and freedoms of the data subject, or (ii) the processing is necessary for the establishment, exercise, or defense of legal claims, then the exception :checks-exception-in-21-1-NW applies. Here, NW stands for not withdraw, indicating that the data subject is not permitted to withdraw their consent. NB. statements108Formula7, statements108Formula8, and statements108Formula9 are again the same SPARQL rule. As explained above for statements108Formula4/5/6, negation-as-failure leads to three separate rules due to different antecedents in the corresponding D-KB rules, but once translated into superiority relations, they collapse into a single rule.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements108Formula7/statements108Formula8/statements108Formula9"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?exx :defeats-on-21-1-NW ?ex. ?exx :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula7/statements108Formula8/statements108Formula9"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?ex :checks-exception-in-21-1-NW (?ep ?w ?y). {?ep :is-related-to ?k. ?k rdf:type :LegalClaim.}UNION{?eov rdf:type :Rexist. ?eov rdf:type :Override. ?eov :has-agent ?lg. ?eov :has-object ?rf. ?lg :legitimate-grounds-of ?y. ?rf :rights-and-freedoms-of ?w.}. BIND(BNode() AS ?exx) NOT EXISTS{?exxr :defeats-on-21-1-NW ?ex. ?exxr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements108Formula7/statements108Formula8/statements108Formula9"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements275Formula1 (gdprC9A89P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the purpose on which the personal data processing is based is 'public interest', 'research', or 'statistics', then the processor must safeguard the rights and freedoms of the data subject.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements275Formula1"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?es rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?es rdf:type :Safeguard. ?es :has-time ?t1. ?es :has-agent ?x. ?es :has-object ?rf. ?es :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements275Formula1"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?epu rdf:type :PIorRorS. ?rf :rights-and-freedoms-of ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?es) NOT EXISTS{?esr rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?esr rdf:type :Safeguard. ?esr :has-time ?t1. ?esr :has-agent ?x. ?esr :has-object ?rf. ?esr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements275Formula1"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements275Formula2 (gdprC9A89P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the purpose on which the personal data processing is based is 'public interest', 'research', or 'statistics', and there is a measure ':m' that causes/enables both the processing and the non-identification of the data subject, then the processor must implement that measure.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements275Formula2"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ei rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?ei rdf:type :Implement. ?ei :has-time ?t1. ?ei :has-agent ?x. ?ei :has-object ?m. ?ei :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements275Formula2"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?w rdf:type :DataSubject. ?z :personaldata-of ?w. ?y :controller-of ?z. ?x rdf:type :Processor. ?edp rdf:type :Rexist. ?edp rdf:type :Nominates. ?edp :has-time ?t1. ?edp :has-agent ?y. ?edp :has-object ?x. ?ep rdf:type :Rexist. ?ep rdf:type :ProcessPersonalData. ?ep :has-time ?t1. ?ep :has-agent ?x. ?ep :has-object ?z. ?epu rdf:type :Purpose. ?ep :is-based-on ?epu. ?epu rdf:type :PIorRorS. ?m rdf:type :Measure. ?m :cause ?ep. ?m :cause ?enid. ?enid :not ?eid. ?eid rdf:type :Identify. ?eid :has-object ?w. BIND(BNode() AS ?ei) NOT EXISTS{?eir rdf:type :M-Obligatory. ?eir rdf:type :Implement. ?eir :has-time ?t1. ?eir :has-agent ?x. ?eir :has-object ?m. ?eir :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements275Formula2"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].

#D-KB ID: statements275Formula3 (gdprC9A89P1ref)
#DESCRIPTION: If the purpose of the personal data processing is public interest, research, or statistical in nature, then the obligation described in statements5Formula1 does not apply. That obligation requires the data controller to store personal data in a form that no longer permits the identification of the data subject once the data are no longer needed for the original processing purpose. This exception therefore means that, where the purpose is public interest, research, or statistics, personal data may be retained beyond that point. However, the two preceding obligations apply: the rights and freedoms of the data subject must still be safeguarded at all times.
[rdf:type :InferenceRule; :has-dkb-id "statements275Formula3"^^xsd:string; :has-sparql-code """
	CONSTRUCT{?ex :defeats-on-89-1 ?ek. ?ex :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements275Formula3"^^xsd:string.}
	WHERE{?ek :checks-exception-in-89-1 (?epu). ?epu rdf:type :PIorRorS. BIND(BNode() AS ?ex) NOT EXISTS{?exr :defeats-on-89-1 ?ek. ?exr :has-generating-dkb-rule-id "statements275Formula3"^^xsd:string.}}"""^^xsd:string].
